    <updated>2017-02-18T16:15:19.000Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><head><script src="https://cdn.plot.ly/plotly-latest.min.js"></script><script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/numeric/1.2.6/numeric.min.js"></script></head><br>This is a test of using <a href="https://plot.ly/" target="_blank" rel="external">Plotly</a> in my blog.  </p>
<h2 id="interactive-plots-in-plotlyjs"><a href="#Interactive-plots-in-plotly-js" class="headerlink" title="Interactive plots in plotly.js"></a>Interactive plots in plotly.js</h2><p>Two graphs are depicted as follows: </p>
<h3 id="a-simple-line-graph"><a href="#A-simple-line-graph" class="headerlink" title="A simple line graph"></a>A simple line graph</h3><div id="tester" style="width:600px;height:250px;margin: 0px auto;"></div>

<script>
    TESTER = document.getElementById('tester');
    Plotly.plot( TESTER, [{
    x: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5],
    y: [1, 2, 4, 8, 16] }], {
    margin: { t: 0 } } );
</script>

<a id="more"></a>
<h3 id="mixed-subplots"><a href="#Mixed-subplots" class="headerlink" title="Mixed subplots"></a>Mixed subplots</h3> <div id="myDiv" style="width: 540px; height: 403px; margin: 0px auto;">

<script src="/plotly/mixed_subplot.js">

<h2 id="Note"><a href="#Note" class="headerlink" title="Note"></a>Note</h2><ul>
<li>The interactive plots make the browser load much slower, especially the second complex one;</li>
<li>Two methods of inserting graphs were used above: the former with <code>.js</code> file and the file containing data directly written in the <code>.md</code> file; the latter with links pointing to the <code>.js</code> file outside the current directory;</li>
<li>Later, the <a href="http://www.chartjs.org/">Chart.js</a> and <a href="https://d3js.org/">D3.js</a> will also be used to test the performance. </li>
</ul>
<h2 id="Reference"><a href="#Reference" class="headerlink" title="Reference"></a>Reference</h2><ol>
<li><a href="https://plot.ly/javascript/getting-started/">Getting Started with plotly.js</a></li>
<li><a href="https://plot.ly/javascript/mixed-subplots/">Mixed Subplots in plotly.js</a></li>
</ol>
</script></div>]]></content>
    
